pr_title: Added clang-format tools and jq to general-worker
pr_body:
Added the following
- clang-format
- git-clang-format
- jq
- link python command to python3
This PR proposes to add concourse-resources which contain code for building and pushing gerrit-resource to the dockerhub. gerrit-resource can be used to fetch gerrit repo for every new patchset.

It does only seem to check style once the commit is in master though?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 5, 20, 44, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'kallisti5', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 683774655, 'comment_body': 'good idea to leverage the smaller general-worker here vs the full toolchain container. efficient!', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 5, 20, 44, 59, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'kallisti5', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 684247643, 'comment_body': 'https://github.com/haiku/infrastructure/blob/5f1bcbe80bc29ce20cdb9d76bae35df12db5ce49/concourse/pipelines/checker-bot.yml#L13-L18

I see in our gerrit code review website, the default search query is `status:open -is:wip`
What do you suggest to put in the query?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 6, 13, 45, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'HrithikKumar49', 'type': 'User'}]
